SIMPLE: observatory
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Observatory
<hw>Ob*serv"a*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Observatories</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>observatoire</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A place or building for
making observations on the heavenly bodies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The new <qex>observatory</qex> in Greenwich Park.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A building fitted with instruments for making
systematic observations of any particular class or series of natural
phenomena.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A place, as an elevated chamber, from which a view
may be observed or commanded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A lookout on a flank of a battery
whence an officer can note the range and effect of the fire; usually
referred to as an <altname>observation post</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Farrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Observe</ent>⟦br⟧
